Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Combine feta cheese and bread crumbs; set aside. Remove almond packet from beans; set aside. Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook onion and garlic 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in oregano, red pepper and tomatoes. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir in green beans; simmer 3 minutes longer. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with feta topping and slivered almonds. Bake 10 minutes or until crust is browned and green beans are heated through.